# Commercial DB Audit Playbook

## Quick start

```bash
python scripts/commercial_db_audit.py --project <BQ_PROJECT_ID>
```

This runs all 11 analysis sections and generates an HTML report to `analysis_notebooks/reports/output/`.

## Options

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--project` | (required) | BigQuery project to audit |
| `--billing-project` | `cred-1556636033881` | Project that runs queries / has `cred_seed` |
| `--schemas` | `commercial_model_prod commercial_credentity cred_enrichment` | Key schemas to analyse |
| `--output` | Auto-generated | Custom output path for the HTML report |

## Authentication

Requires Google Cloud + Drive scopes. If the user hits `Forbidden: Permission denied while getting Drive credentials`:
```bash
gcloud auth application-default login \
  --scopes='https://www.googleapis.com/auth/cloud-platform,https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive.readonly'
```

## What it does (11 sections)

1. Schema inventory (INFORMATION_SCHEMA.SCHEMATA + COLUMNS)
2. Table volumes (TABLE_STORAGE — row counts, storage)
3. CRM plan gap analysis (DataDescriptionMetadata — tier table with expansion candidates)
4. Core CRM tables (Account, Contact, Activity — counts + null rates)
5. User events & collections
6. Unipile/LinkedIn status
7. Person enrichment coverage (field-level %)
8. Company enrichment coverage (field-level %)
9. Data sources (cred_seed.DataSources)
10. Unique data points vs standard CRMs
11. HTML report generation with Chart.js charts

## Answers these questions

- **Q1**: What are all the integrated data sources? → Sections 1, 7-8, 9
- **Q2**: What data points can we expose per CRM tier? → Section 3 (full tier table)
- **Q3**: Are there unique data points? → Section 10

## Error handling

The script uses `safe_query()` — if a section fails (missing table, permission error), it logs a warning and continues. The report will show available data and skip failed sections.

## For deeper exploration

The template notebook is at `analysis_notebooks/CommercialDBAnalysis/commercial_db_audit_template.ipynb` for interactive investigation after the script runs.
